From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: cunyuan <cunyuan.liu@cixtech.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Sep 2025 16:59:11 +0800
Subject: DPTSW-19618: [linlon-dp] Set AFBC 32x8 to the highest priority in the
 supported modifier lists

For AFBC buffers with width exceeding 2048, only the 32x8 block size is supported.

Because some display services select the first modifier supported by the plane,
the AFBC_32x8 (_TILED | _SC | _SPLIT | _SPARSE | _YTR) modifier is moved to the
top of the supported modifiers list.

This gives it the highest priority and ensures proper handling of wide AFBC buffers.

Signed-off-by: cunyuan.liu <cunyuan.liu@cixtech.com>
Change-Id: I2c6bc8b62247ab84b01dea89ac8b6f8ae039bb90
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_format_caps.c | 7 ++++++-
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_format_caps.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_format_caps.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_format_caps.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_format_caps.c
@@ -60,6 +60,12 @@ u32 linlondp_get_afbc_format_bpp(const struct drm_format_info *info,
  * 2. Tiled RGB always has SC
  */
 u64 linlondp_supported_modifiers[] = {
+	/* For AFBC buffers with a width exceeding 2048,
+	 * only the 32x8 block size is supported.
+	 * So, AFBC 32x8 is set to the highest priority here.
+	*/
+	/* TILED + SC + SPLIT + SPLIT + SPARSE + YTR */
+	AFBC_32x8(_TILED | _SC | _SPLIT | _SPARSE | _YTR),
 	/* AFBC_16x16 + features: YUV+RGB both */
 	AFBC_16x16(0),
 	/* SPARSE */
@@ -83,7 +89,6 @@ u64 linlondp_supported_modifiers[] = {
 	/* split mode is only allowed for sparse mode */
 	AFBC_32x8(_SPLIT | _SPARSE | _YTR),
 	/* TILED + SC + (SPLIT+SPARSE | SPARSE) + YTR */
-	AFBC_32x8(_TILED | _SC | _SPLIT | _SPARSE | _YTR),
 	AFBC_32x8(_TILED | _SC | _SPARSE | _YTR),
 	AFBC_32x8(_TILED | _SC | _YTR), DRM_FORMAT_MOD_LINEAR,
 	DRM_FORMAT_MOD_INVALID
